{
  "schema": "v1",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Create in Me a Clean Heart, O God"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "text": "For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David. When Nathan the prophet came to him after his adultery with Bathsheba."
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 1 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Have mercy on me, O God," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "according to Your loving devotion;" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "according to Your great compassion," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "blot out my transgressions." }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 2 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Wash me clean of my iniquity" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "and cleanse me from my sin." }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 3 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "For I know my transgressions," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and my sin is always before me." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 4 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Against You, You only, have I sinned" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and done what is evil in Your sight," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "so that You may be proved right when You speak"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "and blameless when You judge." }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 5 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Surely I was brought forth in iniquity;" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "I was sinful when my mother conceived me." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 6 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "Surely You desire truth in the inmost being;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "You teach me wisdom in the inmost place." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 7 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "Purify me with hyssop, and I will be clean;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "wash me, and I will be whiter than snow." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 8 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Let me hear joy and gladness;" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "let the bones You have crushed rejoice." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 9 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Hide Your face from my sins" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and blot out all my iniquities." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 10 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Create in me a clean heart, O God," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and renew a right spirit within me." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 11 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Cast me not away from Your presence;" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "take not Your Holy Spirit from me." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 12 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Restore to me the joy of Your salvation," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and sustain me with a willing spirit." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 13 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "Then I will teach transgressors Your ways,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and sinners will return to You." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 14 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "Deliver me from bloodguilt, O God," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "the God of my salvation," }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "and my tongue will sing of Your righteousness."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 15 },
            { "kind": "t", "text": "O Lord, open my lips," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "and my mouth will declare Your praise." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 16 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "For You do not delight in sacrifice, or I would bring it;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "You take no pleasure in burnt offerings." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 17 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "a broken and a contrite heart," }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "O God, You will not despise." }]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "poetry",
      "lines": [
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 18 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "In Your good pleasure, cause Zion to prosper;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "build up the walls of Jerusalem." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 0,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "v", "n": 19 },
            {
              "kind": "t",
              "text": "Then You will delight in righteous sacrifices,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [{ "kind": "t", "text": "in whole burnt offerings;" }]
        },
        {
          "indent": 1,
          "segments": [
            { "kind": "t", "text": "then bulls will be offered on Your altar." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
